# Activity documentation (mandatory)

- Every meaningful agent/subagent action must be documented — chat memory is not sufficient.
- Applies to **Cursor and Antigravity** (and any other provider).
- Append to `workflow/activity/ACTIVITY-LOG.md` (when, session id, **provider**, role, action, target, result, evidence).
- Promote work also writes role folders under `H:\releases\...\evidence\`.
- **Promote ACTIVITY-LOG rows must mention app git tag and dependency versions/tags** (CONSCIOUS #13).
- Update `workflow/sessions.md` outcomes for milestones.
- **Update product/ops docs after meaningful actions** (CONSCIOUS #12) — OPS/README/platform/DEPLOY; same turn when practical. Activity log alone is not enough for how-to knowledge.
- Never log secrets/tokens/passwords.
- Details: `workflow/activity/README.md` · Entry: `AGENTS.md` · Standing order: `workflow/CONSCIOUS.md` rules 12–13
